Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper addresses concerns related to privacy and security in IoT environments, proposing a framework to ensure trust in IoT systems and applications. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions the use of secure log sealing on live sensor data to produce a verifiable 'proof-of-integrity,' which could be considered a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the deployment of a smart space system (TIPPERS) that provides real-time location-based services, which could involve distributed computing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a framework (IoT Notary) to ensure trust in IoT systems and applications, which could be considered a software engineering solution. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the deployment of a smart space system (TIPPERS) that provides various real-time location-based services, which could involve systems and control.
